{{infobox WorldScouting | type = | name = Council of Protestants in Guiding and Scouting | image = Council of Protestants in Guiding and Scouting.svg | image-size = | caption = | headquarters = | location = | country = International | f-date = | founder = | award-for = | members = | chiefscouttitle = Chairman | chiefscout = Ms. Annette von Stockhausen, Germany | chiefscouttitle2 = | chiefscout2 = | owner = | website = {{URL|cpgs.info}} }}
The '''Council of Protestants in Guiding and Scouting''' ('''CPGS''') is an autonomous, international body committed to promoting and supporting Protestant Scout and Guide associations and to be a link between the [[Scouting|Scout movement]] and [[Protestant churches]] based on the definition of the [[World Council of Churches]] (WCC).
It enjoys consultative status with the [[World Scout Committee]] and forms the [[World Scout Inter-religious Forum]] (WSIF)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wsis2009.org/scouting_wsif.php |title=World Scout Inter-religious Forum (WSIF) |accessdate=2010-01-08 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090413023825/http://wsis2009.org/scouting_wsif.php |archivedate=April 13, 2009 }}</ref> together with the [[International Link of Orthodox Christian Scouts]], [[International Catholic Conference of Scouting]], [[International Union of Muslim Scouts]], International Forum of Jewish Scouts, Won-Buddhism Scout and [[World Buddhist Scout Brotherhood]].
== History == The CPGS was founded as ''Conference on Christianity in Guiding and Scouting'' (CCGS) in 1965. In 2006 it was renamed to ''Council of Protestants in Guiding and Scouting'' reflecting a change of policy within the [[World Organization of the Scout Movement]].
== Members == The members of the CPGS are:<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cpgs.info/members/ |publisher=Council of Protestants in Guiding and Scouting |title=Members |date=|accessdate=15 April 2018}}</ref> * [[Scouting and Guiding in Argentina|Argentina]]: [[Scouts de Argentina]], Comisión Pastoral Scout Cristiano Evangélica * [[Scouting and Guiding in Cameroon|Cameroon]]: [[Les Scouts du Cameroun]] * [[Scouting and Guiding in Denmark|Denmark]]: ** [[Danske Baptisters Spejderkorps]] ** [[KFUM-Spejderne i Danmark]] * [[Scouting and Guiding in Finland|Finland]]: [[The Guides and Scouts of Finland|Suomen Partiolaiset - Finlands Scouter ry]] * [[Scouting and Guiding in France|France]]: [[Eclaireuses et Eclaireurs Unionistes de France]] * [[Scouting and Guiding in Germany|Germany]]: [[Verband Christlicher Pfadfinderinnen und Pfadfinder]] * [[Scouting and Guiding in Hungary|Hungary]]: ICHTHÜSZ – Protestant unit of the [[Magyar Cserkészszövetség|Hungarian Scout Association]] * [[Scouting and Guiding in Ivory Coast|Ivory Coast]]: ** Éclaireuses et Éclaireurs Unionistes de Côte d’Ivoire ** Éclaireuses et Éclaireurs de Côte d’Ivoire (associate member) ** [[Fédération Ivoirienne du Scoutisme]] (observer)
