'''Sacred caves''' and [[peak sanctuaries]] are characteristic holy places of ancient [[Minoan civilization|Minoan]] Crete. Most scholars agree that sacred caves were used by the Minoans for religious rites. While all peak sanctuaries have clay human figurines, only Idaeon and Psychro have them among the sacred caves. Clay body parts, also called [[votive]] body parts, common among [[peak sanctuaries]], appear in no caves with the exception of a bronze leg in Psychro.
==List of sacred caves== * [[Arkalochori]] * [[Cave of Zeus]] * Inatos * [[Kamares, Crete|Kamares]] * [[Mameloukou]] * [[Phaneromeni]] * [[Psychro Cave]] (also called the Diktaean Cave) * [[Skotino cave|Skotino]]
==References== * Jones, Donald W. 1999 ''Peak Sanctuaries and Sacred Caves of Minoan Crete'' {{ISBN|91-7081-153-9}}
