'''Tek Singh''' was a [[Sikh]] religious figure. [[Toba Tek Singh]] a Pakistani city from [[Punjab, Pakistan|Punjab]] is named after him.<ref name="auto">{{cite web|url=http://www.dawn.com/news/1017306|title=The story of Toba Tek Singh|first=Muhammad Hassan|last=Miraj|date=10 June 2013|publisher=}}</ref>

There is a legend associated with him that he was very kind-hearted man who served water and provided shelter to the worn out and thirsty travelers passing by a small pond ("toba" in Punjabi) which eventually was called Toba Tek Singh.<ref name="auto"/>

